Lists precursor masses of all molecules in library

get_precursors.Rd

Lists precursor masses of all molecules in library

get_precursors(libs)

Arguments

libs

Which libraries to match against. Should be the output of [get_libs] or [create_lib].

Value

Data frame with three columns: file (name of library), name (Molecule name) and prec_mz (M/Z of the molecule precursor).

Examples

libs = get_libs()
precs = get_precursors(libs)
head(precs)
#> # A tibble: 6 x 4
#>   file       class_name    name         prec_mz
#>   <chr>      <chr>         <chr>          <dbl>
#> 1 AcCa_H.csv Acylcarnitine AcCar(0)+H      162.
#> 2 AcCa_H.csv Acylcarnitine AcCar(2:0)+H    204.
#> 3 AcCa_H.csv Acylcarnitine AcCar(3:0)+H    218.
#> 4 AcCa_H.csv Acylcarnitine AcCar(4:0)+H    232.
#> 5 AcCa_H.csv Acylcarnitine AcCar(5:1)+H    244.
#> 6 AcCa_H.csv Acylcarnitine AcCar(5:0)+H    246.
